WEBVTT

00:01.653 --> 00:03.177
- Previously, on "You"...

00:03.220 --> 00:05.222
- Everyone just calls me Beck.
And you're...

00:05.266 --> 00:07.181
Joe?
- Goldberg.

00:07.224 --> 00:09.139
A guy needs to
protect himself,

00:09.183 --> 00:12.099
and your name was
a glorious place to start.

00:12.142 --> 00:14.188
The next thing our little
friend the internet gave me

00:14.231 --> 00:15.537
was your address.

00:15.580 --> 00:17.147
[suspenseful music]

00:17.191 --> 00:18.757
- Uhh!

00:18.801 --> 00:21.717
- Maybe we could get
a drink sometime?

00:21.760 --> 00:22.761
- Sure.

00:22.805 --> 00:24.067
- Hey, let me up.

00:24.111 --> 00:26.374
[whispering]
Oh, you make me insane.

00:26.417 --> 00:28.680
- Oh, Beck, who is this?

00:28.724 --> 00:31.074
Benjamin J. Ashby.
Greenwich born,

00:31.118 --> 00:32.206
boarding school bred.

00:32.249 --> 00:34.077
After you.
- All right.

00:34.121 --> 00:35.992
Man, I'm thinkin' maybe--

00:37.254 --> 00:38.908
Do not tell me
that you're doing this

00:38.951 --> 00:40.214
because of Beck!

00:40.257 --> 00:42.129
- I'm very scared
of what you would do to her.

00:42.172 --> 00:44.653
- She show you her ladle? She's
got this red kitchen ladle.

00:44.696 --> 00:47.134
It's a whole "call you Daddy,
spank me" thing.

00:47.177 --> 00:48.874
- Benji, I'd love your help.

00:48.918 --> 00:52.139
Unfortunately, I know
you're a pathological liar.

00:52.182 --> 00:53.923
- [gasps, wheezes]

00:53.966 --> 00:57.013
- I just knew Benji
was the worst kind of poison,

00:57.057 --> 00:59.363
so I did what I had to do
to help you.

00:59.407 --> 01:01.365
[dramatic musical sting]

01:01.409 --> 01:05.021
[light music]

01:05.065 --> 01:10.505
♪

01:10.548 --> 01:12.594
Joe: It's been three days...

01:12.637 --> 01:14.248
- [laughs]
- Since our first kiss,

01:14.291 --> 01:16.337
and I have to say...
things are looking

01:16.380 --> 01:18.469
pretty good for us
post-Benji.

01:18.513 --> 01:20.123
- If you could only watch
one movie

01:20.167 --> 01:22.125
for the rest of your life,
what would it be?

01:22.169 --> 01:23.387
- "Beverly Hills Cop."

01:23.431 --> 01:25.520
- Really?
- Oh, yeah. Dead serious.

01:25.563 --> 01:28.871
- Okay...I'll bite.
Enlighten me.

01:28.914 --> 01:31.352
- Well, it's funny,
but the danger...

01:31.395 --> 01:33.180
feels very real.
- [laughs]

01:33.223 --> 01:34.485
- It checks all the boxes.

01:34.529 --> 01:37.227
What's yours?
What's your forever movie?

01:37.271 --> 01:40.230
- Mm.
I'd have to go with...

01:40.274 --> 01:41.710
"Pretty In Pink."

01:41.753 --> 01:43.581
- Invisible townie girl
swept off her feet

01:43.625 --> 01:46.497
by the one guy
who really sees her.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.151
A little on the nose, Beck.

01:48.195 --> 01:50.501
I love that movie.

01:50.545 --> 01:52.721
I'll be that guy,
the one who sees you.

01:52.764 --> 01:54.636
You deserve that,
after Benji.

01:54.679 --> 01:56.638
- So...

01:56.681 --> 01:58.770
your...old girlfriend,

01:58.814 --> 02:01.382
the girl at Peach's party
was talking about...

02:01.425 --> 02:03.471
Candace, is it?
- It's customary...

02:03.514 --> 02:05.603
the inventory
of past heartbreak.

02:05.647 --> 02:07.301
- Do I wanna know?
- But Candace--

02:07.344 --> 02:09.346
I'm not sure
how to tell you about her yet.

02:09.390 --> 02:11.261
It's too soon, Beck.

02:11.305 --> 02:13.959
I mean, I'm an open book,
but it's--it's the old story.

02:14.003 --> 02:17.398
Just...thinking you're right
for someone...

02:17.441 --> 02:18.834
and you're not.

02:18.877 --> 02:21.053
- Hmm. I got about
a dozen of those.

02:21.097 --> 02:24.318
- Hmm.
- Maybe sometime over a drink.

02:24.361 --> 02:26.189
- Or ten.
- [laughs]

02:26.233 --> 02:27.799
- Yep.
- Ten?

02:27.843 --> 02:30.019
- Ten. Ten...
- [laughs]

02:30.062 --> 02:31.629
- Give or take.

02:31.673 --> 02:34.893
[light music]

02:34.937 --> 02:39.289
♪

02:39.333 --> 02:41.378
- I want to come in, I do.

02:41.422 --> 02:43.424
But I'm gonna make us wait.

02:43.467 --> 02:45.295
You're worth waiting for.
Besides...

02:45.339 --> 02:46.731
Bye.

02:46.775 --> 02:48.298
Right now, I have something

02:48.342 --> 02:51.171
rather pressing to deal with.

02:54.304 --> 02:57.220
[dark music]

02:57.264 --> 02:59.918
♪

02:59.962 --> 03:02.051
Nothing sweeter than
townie pie.

03:02.094 --> 03:03.618
#MuffinGrabNGo.

03:06.316 --> 03:09.928
[dark music continues]

03:09.972 --> 03:17.109
♪

03:18.198 --> 03:20.461
[phone chimes]

03:20.504 --> 03:22.376
Beck: Grab N Go? Really?

03:22.419 --> 03:23.681
Townie Pie? What the--

03:23.725 --> 03:26.510
You're dead to me, Benji.
Dead.

03:27.642 --> 03:29.252
Joe: You're finally moving on.

03:29.296 --> 03:31.167
And now that you've
dealt with Benji,

03:31.211 --> 03:34.518
it's time for me
to do the same.

03:34.562 --> 03:37.521
[dark music swells]

03:37.565 --> 03:46.095
♪

03:46.138 --> 03:49.751
How exactly does one
get rid of a body?

03:49.794 --> 03:51.709
I can't just Google
this kind of thing

03:51.753 --> 03:54.277
without creating a pretty
damning evidence trail.

03:54.321 --> 03:56.975
So I turn to those
I trust most for tips--

03:57.019 --> 04:00.283
King, Carr, Franzen, Flynn.

04:00.327 --> 04:02.416
Fun fact:
spatchcocking a chicken

04:02.459 --> 04:03.765
and dismembering a human

04:03.808 --> 04:06.420
involve the same six
essential steps.

04:06.463 --> 04:08.117
Not sure I'm down for that.

04:08.160 --> 04:09.945
Little intense.
But...

04:09.988 --> 04:12.600
I think I finally have
a plan for Benji.

04:13.601 --> 04:15.472
- Oh, hey, Joe, I didn't know
you were up there.

04:15.516 --> 04:17.953
Do you mind if I play
some, uh, Enrique Iglesias?

04:17.996 --> 04:19.650
I'm trying to
bone up on my Spanish.

04:19.694 --> 04:21.304
- These are officially
the darkest days...

04:21.348 --> 04:22.958
Sounds great.
In the history of the world.

04:23.001 --> 04:24.394
- I mean, I can pick
something else.

04:24.438 --> 04:25.700
I got a ton of playlists
on here.

04:25.743 --> 04:28.703
I got rock music,
club music, jazz music.

04:28.746 --> 04:30.748
- I wonder if he's a virgin.
Stick with the Iglesias.

04:30.792 --> 04:32.489
I'm just gonna be in the
basement working on some books.

04:32.533 --> 04:33.795
I don't wanna be disturbed.

04:33.838 --> 04:35.318
All right?
- No problem.

04:35.362 --> 04:36.537
Thanks, Joe!

04:36.580 --> 04:38.278
- Here's what I know.

04:38.321 --> 04:41.281
There can be no dead Benji
for you to mourn.

04:41.324 --> 04:42.804
He needs to disappear.

04:42.847 --> 04:45.937
Already handled the optics
on social media--

04:45.981 --> 04:49.506
portrait of a dude hard
partying his way off the grid.

04:49.550 --> 04:51.856
As for the body--

04:51.900 --> 04:54.511
cremation seems expedient.

04:54.555 --> 04:56.339
This will require chemicals,

04:56.383 --> 05:00.778
a steady blaze, and absolutely
no dental records.

05:00.822 --> 05:04.042
[tense music]

05:04.086 --> 05:07.742
♪

05:07.785 --> 05:09.483
[mallet thuds on floor]

05:09.526 --> 05:11.528
Bluuh...
[liquid splashes]

05:11.572 --> 05:13.313
[coughs]
It looks like

05:13.356 --> 05:17.055
I'm gonna need to slow
the biological roll on Benji.

05:17.099 --> 05:19.057
It's about temperature,
and it's about humidity.

05:19.101 --> 05:22.670
And dropping the temp this low
puts the books at risk--

05:22.713 --> 05:25.847
dry, brittle, lost forever.

05:25.890 --> 05:28.502
My humidifiers
won't let that happen.

05:28.545 --> 05:30.373
Gertrude Stein is dead.

05:30.417 --> 05:33.507
She's not coming back
to sign books.

05:33.550 --> 05:36.510
Hopefully, this holds him
until I can man up

05:36.553 --> 05:38.250
and do the deed.

05:38.294 --> 05:39.164
[light knocking]

05:39.208 --> 05:40.905
- Come in.
- Hi...there.

05:40.949 --> 05:43.430
I'm, uh...
Guinevere Beck.

05:43.473 --> 05:45.432
I'm your new MFA transfer.

05:45.475 --> 05:49.479
Professor Leahy and I agreed,
uh, that it would be bet--

05:49.523 --> 05:51.307
Oh, sorry.

05:51.351 --> 05:54.397
Um, I'm looking for
Professor Mott?

05:54.441 --> 05:55.659
- Beck, is it?

05:55.703 --> 05:57.531
- Yes, hi.
- Blythe.

05:57.574 --> 05:59.576
- [gasps]
- I heard you were joining us.

05:59.620 --> 06:01.535
- Yeah.
- We meet here for workshop

06:01.578 --> 06:02.971
on Tuesdays and Thursdays.

06:03.014 --> 06:05.539
Mott's no Leahy, though,
so bring your A game.

06:05.582 --> 06:07.236
- I intend to.

06:07.279 --> 06:09.673
You know, I actually--
I read one of your essays

06:09.717 --> 06:11.545
in the "Review" last month,

06:11.588 --> 06:14.417
and it was so illuminating.
I tweeted it.

06:14.461 --> 06:18.465
- Social Media. It's like
the next great genocide.

06:20.684 --> 06:22.599
Jersey, right?
- Sorry?

06:22.643 --> 06:23.992
- It's where you're from?

06:24.035 --> 06:26.734
- No, I'm, uh,
I'm from Nantucket.

06:26.777 --> 06:28.910
- Oh, interesting.

06:30.564 --> 06:32.566
- Where are you from?
- Such a tough question.

06:32.609 --> 06:34.959
Um...I was born
in Papua New Guinea,

06:35.003 --> 06:37.614
but my dad worked
for the State Department,

06:37.658 --> 06:39.137
so we moved around a lot.

06:39.181 --> 06:40.443
Actually separated from
my parents at one point.

06:40.487 --> 06:42.532
Did some modeling
in Tokyo.

06:42.576 --> 06:45.840
My hair
is super-unique there.

06:45.883 --> 06:47.668
[both chuckle]
[phone buzzes]

06:47.711 --> 06:50.584
[buzzing]

06:50.627 --> 06:52.107
[stops buzzing]

06:53.195 --> 06:55.937
[speaking Swedish]

06:57.155 --> 06:59.636
I'm sorry,
it's my grandparents.

06:59.680 --> 07:00.898
I'll see you
in class, okay?

07:00.942 --> 07:02.683
- Okay.
- Okay.

07:02.726 --> 07:05.120
Hey...
[laughs]

07:05.163 --> 07:06.251
Yeah.

07:06.295 --> 07:07.862
- And then she walked away,

07:07.905 --> 07:09.559
and I melted into the earth.

07:09.603 --> 07:11.648
- Sounds like a pretentious
bitch, if you ask me.

07:11.692 --> 07:13.433
- No. Blythe's amazing.

07:13.476 --> 07:15.783
She wrote this piece
about how she and her mother

07:15.826 --> 07:18.699
got bulimia together
while in Italy, and she was 12!

07:18.742 --> 07:20.701
- Chic.
- What the--

07:20.744 --> 07:23.355
Is that a nose?
- It's a dick pic, Annika.

07:23.399 --> 07:25.619
- [laughs]
- So what? It's just zoomed in.

07:25.662 --> 07:29.013
- No!
- Why's it against shag carpet?

07:29.057 --> 07:30.450
- I don't know.
- Perspective?

07:30.493 --> 07:31.668
- I don't get it.

07:31.712 --> 07:33.844
I mean, why do men think
disembodied members

07:33.888 --> 07:35.629
equal foreplay?
You know, they're not

07:35.672 --> 07:38.109
aesthetically pleasing.
- Ooh! I disagree.

07:38.153 --> 07:39.981
I have over 200
saved on my phone

07:40.024 --> 07:43.201
organized by category.
It's my Guggenheim.

07:43.245 --> 07:44.681
- [chuckling]

07:44.725 --> 07:46.509
Fat bats.

07:46.553 --> 07:47.771
Boomerangs.

07:47.815 --> 07:49.556
Banana boats.

07:49.599 --> 07:51.601
Late bloomers.

07:51.645 --> 07:52.950
And Jewish guys.

07:52.994 --> 07:54.474
- More power to 'em,
but your friends

07:54.517 --> 07:56.258
kinda treat sex
like it means nothing.

07:56.301 --> 07:57.738
- Till she sees
his junk in zoom!

07:57.781 --> 07:59.696
- But you're different,
aren't you?

07:59.740 --> 08:01.132
- Honestly,
I see her point.

08:01.176 --> 08:02.569
I hooked up with
some guy last night.

08:02.612 --> 08:06.181
Knee deep in before I realized
he's uncircumcised.

08:06.224 --> 08:07.748
- Ooh!
- It kind of looked like...

08:07.791 --> 08:10.185
I don't know, a...hoodie?
- Whoa!

08:10.228 --> 08:12.100
- Bookstore clerk
has a turtleneck?

08:12.143 --> 08:14.102
- Bookstore manager,
but, no, not Joe.

08:14.145 --> 08:16.844
Some guy from Tinder.
Just a little down and dirty.

08:16.887 --> 08:18.759
You know?
- Wow!

08:18.802 --> 08:20.978
- Joe is still a maybe.

08:21.022 --> 08:23.546
- A maybe?
I'm amaybe?

08:23.590 --> 08:25.200
And you're still screwing
other guys?

08:25.243 --> 08:26.854
Beck!
How did I miss this?

08:26.897 --> 08:29.509
How did I read this
so completely wrong?

08:29.552 --> 08:31.772
- Look, if you wanna bone
Benji outta your system,

08:31.815 --> 08:33.600
more power to you.

08:33.643 --> 08:36.559
I just wanna make sure that
you're respecting yourself.

08:36.603 --> 08:39.693
Look, I'm just saying...

08:39.736 --> 08:43.000
are you being your most
amazing self right now?

08:43.044 --> 08:45.655
- I mean, this is...
this is my process.

08:45.699 --> 08:48.136
It's like a Benji exorcism.

08:48.179 --> 08:51.661
I'm just exploring
my options in a city of...

08:51.705 --> 08:53.358
8 million people.

08:53.402 --> 08:55.404
It's only reasonable, right?
- Yeah.

08:55.447 --> 08:56.710
- I'm gonna get a drink.

08:56.753 --> 09:00.801
[pop music in background]

09:00.844 --> 09:02.237
- I like your tattoo.

09:03.499 --> 09:05.153
- I don't have a tattoo.

09:05.196 --> 09:07.459
- Love is patient and kind.
[Beck moaning]

09:07.503 --> 09:08.896
And so am I, Beck.

09:08.939 --> 09:11.246
For you, I can be patient.

09:11.289 --> 09:13.074
Maybe this is your process.

09:13.117 --> 09:14.945
Nobody buys the first pair
of jeans they try on,

09:14.989 --> 09:16.599
no matter how perfect.

09:16.643 --> 09:19.733
But as much as I'm hoping
this is just a stage,

09:19.776 --> 09:21.691
