on your iCloud

09:21.735 --> 09:24.651
has revealed a swipe-fest
of millennial man-boys.

09:24.694 --> 09:26.000
Guy with tiger.

09:26.043 --> 09:27.697
Junior William Morris agent.

09:27.741 --> 09:30.134
Viking Wannabe.
You've been a busy girl, Beck.

09:30.178 --> 09:32.528
It's more competition
than I realized.

09:32.572 --> 09:33.660
This thing between us--

09:33.703 --> 09:35.836
it's new, tenuous.

09:35.879 --> 09:38.099
And the cost was a corpse.

09:38.142 --> 09:40.231
But I can't get rid of
every guy in New York.

09:40.275 --> 09:43.017
If I wanna win your heart,
I'm gonna have to show you--

09:43.060 --> 09:45.889
[backboard thumping]
[Beck moaning]

09:45.933 --> 09:46.890
[creak, crack]

09:46.934 --> 09:48.631
- Aah!
[laughs]

09:48.675 --> 09:50.459
- I'm not a "maybe."

09:50.502 --> 09:52.026
I'mThe One.

09:56.770 --> 10:00.600
- It's time.
Time to get rid of Benji

10:00.643 --> 10:03.124
so I can focus
my undivided attention

10:03.167 --> 10:05.735
on you, Beck, on us.

10:05.779 --> 10:07.781
So I'm gonna need
a few supplies.

10:07.824 --> 10:08.869
- Hey, Joe.

10:08.912 --> 10:11.088
You said
you needed to talk?

10:11.132 --> 10:13.047
- I do, yeah.
So here's the thing.

10:13.090 --> 10:15.049
I have a secret project
I'm working on,

10:15.092 --> 10:16.659
but I gotta open up
the shop,

10:16.703 --> 10:18.792
so I thought you could
run some errands for me.

10:18.835 --> 10:20.750
I'll give you a little
money for books.

10:20.794 --> 10:22.447
Just between us.

10:22.491 --> 10:23.840
- Yeah. No problem.

10:23.884 --> 10:25.842
Between us.
What do you need?

10:25.886 --> 10:29.019
- Well, you might have to
run to a few different places.

10:33.894 --> 10:35.983
- You can count on me, Joe.

10:36.026 --> 10:39.682
[dark music]

10:39.726 --> 10:41.249
- Thanks, Pac.

10:43.643 --> 10:46.820
- The swine and I.

10:46.863 --> 10:49.823
Eye to eye.

10:50.954 --> 10:53.870
My heart is his.

10:53.914 --> 10:56.046
And that...

10:56.090 --> 10:57.787
was sunset.

11:03.880 --> 11:05.665
- I'm not sure it had
the vigilance or depth

11:05.708 --> 11:08.798
that you're capable of.
I just wasn't fully invested.

11:08.842 --> 11:11.366
- Interesting, Blythe.

11:11.409 --> 11:13.977
How do we maintain
the reader's attention?

11:14.021 --> 11:16.850
We infuse the universal

11:16.893 --> 11:18.895
with painful specificity,

11:18.939 --> 11:20.418
or they simply turn the page.

11:20.462 --> 11:21.898
- Exactly.

11:21.942 --> 11:25.293
My worst fear--and I'm not
commenting on Yuri's poem,

11:25.336 --> 11:29.123
per se, is not to be bad
but unremarkable.

11:29.166 --> 11:32.213
- Unremarkable.
That is the fear.

11:32.256 --> 11:34.824
I hope this was helpful,
Yuri.

11:34.868 --> 11:36.739
I think that does it
for today.

11:36.783 --> 11:38.872
Next up is...Blythe.

11:38.915 --> 11:40.090
And Beck.

11:40.134 --> 11:42.397
Send a piece of your choosing
to myself

11:42.440 --> 11:44.747
and your fellow classmates,
and we'll review on Thursday.

11:44.791 --> 11:47.968
[lightly edgy music]

11:48.011 --> 11:55.062
♪

12:09.816 --> 12:11.861
[bed creaking]

12:11.905 --> 12:13.428
- Here's what I've gleaned

12:13.471 --> 12:16.170
from this little exercise
in futility, Beck.

12:16.213 --> 12:18.172
You're in no mood to write.

12:18.215 --> 12:20.174
[creak, snap, thud]

12:20.217 --> 12:22.393
- And you need a new bed.

12:22.437 --> 12:24.831
So, hey,
maybe your enthusiastic

12:24.874 --> 12:26.528
but ultimately empty encounter

12:26.571 --> 12:27.834
with that Warby Parker-wearing
mixologist

12:27.877 --> 12:29.531
could work to our advantage.

12:29.574 --> 12:30.880
Any chance you're down
for shopping trip?

12:30.924 --> 12:31.838
I've got time to kill

12:31.881 --> 12:34.536
while Paco's out shopping.

12:37.147 --> 12:39.454
- You read my mind.

12:39.497 --> 12:41.282
- Pick you up in an hour.

12:41.325 --> 12:43.806
But I have to play this
perfectly,

12:43.850 --> 12:45.808
and in order to do that,

12:45.852 --> 12:47.723
I gotta break out
the big gun.

12:47.767 --> 12:49.986
[engine revs]

12:50.030 --> 12:52.293
Mr. Mooney's Buick Skylark.

12:52.336 --> 12:54.425
- ♪ Girl, you think
you got it bad... ♪

12:54.469 --> 12:55.992
- You bound down the stairs
in those tight,

12:56.036 --> 12:57.428
not-too-tight jeans.

12:57.472 --> 12:59.039
You're in flip-flops

12:59.082 --> 13:00.170
and your toenails sparkle

13:00.214 --> 13:01.868
and your hair's in a bun,

13:01.911 --> 13:03.608
and, hey, at least you
don't have any hickeys.

13:03.652 --> 13:05.741
So there's that.

13:05.785 --> 13:09.876
♪

13:09.919 --> 13:13.575
- Oh, my God, I can't
believe this is your car.

13:13.618 --> 13:15.359
You're a lifesaver.

13:15.403 --> 13:17.013
[kiss]
No idea how much

13:17.057 --> 13:19.276
I needed a new bed.

13:22.105 --> 13:25.543
- ♪ Girl, you think
you got it bad... ♪

13:25.587 --> 13:27.719
♪ Do do do do do do do

13:27.763 --> 13:31.332
[engine humming]

13:32.463 --> 13:35.684
[Muzak plays in background]

13:35.727 --> 13:37.207
♪

13:37.251 --> 13:39.340
- New Challenge.

13:39.383 --> 13:42.299
How do I segue this from

13:42.343 --> 13:44.301
browsing glassware to...

13:44.345 --> 13:47.043
"Holy shit! Joe's the one"?

13:49.089 --> 13:50.960
- Weird.
[small laugh]

13:51.004 --> 13:53.702
I have one just like this.

13:53.745 --> 13:55.835
- Yeah, I-I know
all about it.

13:55.878 --> 13:59.099
Benji told me.
- It was my dad's.

13:59.142 --> 14:00.665
- The infamous red ladle.

14:00.709 --> 14:02.667
How you like to be spanked
with it.

14:02.711 --> 14:05.496
Is that what
you really want, Beck?

14:05.540 --> 14:08.891
Is that the guy
you're looking for?

14:08.935 --> 14:11.067
[edgy music]

14:11.111 --> 14:13.374
Just pick one.

14:13.417 --> 14:15.898
It's all cut from the same
hunk of overpriced wood.

14:15.942 --> 14:17.769
- I can't decide.

14:17.813 --> 14:19.728
- People trying to buy some
sort of meaning in their lives

14:19.771 --> 14:22.862
with $60 candles
and sustainable lamps.

14:22.905 --> 14:24.298
They all look
pretty good to me.

14:24.341 --> 14:26.909
- No, I just mean
should I get the queen

14:26.953 --> 14:28.476
or the king-size bed?

14:28.519 --> 14:30.913
- Your bedroom isn't big
enough to fit a king.

14:30.957 --> 14:34.351
- You're right, it's too...

14:34.395 --> 14:37.920
How do you know that?

14:37.964 --> 14:39.704
- It's New York.

14:39.748 --> 14:42.229
No one's bedroom is
big enough to fit a king.

14:42.272 --> 14:44.013
[phone chimes]

14:44.057 --> 14:46.581
- Ugh...

14:46.624 --> 14:47.799
[sighs]

14:47.843 --> 14:49.149
- What's wrong?

14:49.192 --> 14:50.759
- This girl, Blythe,
in workshop,

14:50.802 --> 14:52.848
she just submitted
her short story.

14:54.981 --> 14:56.286
- And?
- And I haven't even

14:56.330 --> 14:58.636
started mine yet,
and it's due tomorrow.

15:00.595 --> 15:03.424
[murmurs]

15:03.467 --> 15:04.947
Hers...

15:04.991 --> 15:06.731
it's brilliant.

15:06.775 --> 15:10.692
It's about a crow that flies
into a woman's house,

15:10.735 --> 15:12.999
runs into the walls,
and leaves blood everywhere.

15:13.042 --> 15:15.610
- That sounds terrible.

15:15.653 --> 15:17.307
- Read it.

15:27.230 --> 15:29.450
Well?

15:31.800 --> 15:33.758
- You might be right.
- Ugh!

15:33.802 --> 15:35.978
I know.

15:40.026 --> 15:41.853
Can I ask you something?

15:41.897 --> 15:43.116
- Anything.

15:43.159 --> 15:46.032
- Promise to tell the truth?

15:46.075 --> 15:47.294
- Scout's honor.

15:47.337 --> 15:50.384
[soft music]

15:50.427 --> 15:52.125
♪

15:52.168 --> 15:55.345
- Do you think...
I'm unremarkable?

15:55.389 --> 16:02.831
♪

16:04.180 --> 16:06.095
- Unremarkable people
don't worry

16:06.139 --> 16:08.576
about being unremarkable.

16:11.187 --> 16:13.581
♪

16:13.624 --> 16:17.237
- ♪ Only for you
we should call it ♪

16:17.280 --> 16:19.152
♪ A straight love affair

16:19.195 --> 16:20.980
♪ I suppose...

16:21.023 --> 16:22.372
- This is it, Beck.

16:22.416 --> 16:23.721
This is the moment
I'm gonna show you

16:23.765 --> 16:25.593
just how remarkable you are.

16:25.636 --> 16:27.334
You want down and dirty,
you got it.

16:27.377 --> 16:29.771
♪

16:29.814 --> 16:32.556
- ♪ Palms that may
hold you... ♪

16:32.600 --> 16:34.558
- [gasps]
[whispers] Stop, Joe, stop!

16:34.602 --> 16:36.082
- What? I--What?
I thought that you--

16:36.125 --> 16:37.431
- That I wanted to get
arrested

16:37.474 --> 16:39.824
while you're going
all bush diver on me in public?

16:39.868 --> 16:42.958
That's not exactly
on my to-do list today.

16:45.482 --> 16:48.268
- I guess I read that wrong.

16:51.097 --> 16:53.838
You haven't made eye contact
for the past ten minutes.

16:53.882 --> 16:56.102
Things couldn't get
any worse right now.

16:56.145 --> 16:59.148
[phone buzzing]

16:59.192 --> 17:01.107
Hello?
- Hey, Joe, it's Ethan.

17:01.150 --> 17:03.065
Ethan from the bookstore.
- Yeah, yeah, I know

17:03.109 --> 17:04.588
who you are, Ethan.

17:04.632 --> 17:08.766
- Right. Thing is,
the power's out. Um...

17:08.810 --> 17:11.334
the electrician says he thinks
the system is overloaded,

17:11.378 --> 17:13.032
but he can't get
to the fuse box because...

17:13.075 --> 17:14.816
- It's in the basement
with a dead body.

17:14.859 --> 17:17.079
- Which is locked.
He thinks he can pop the lock,

17:17.123 --> 17:18.689
but I just wanted to--

17:18.733 --> 17:20.996
- No! No, no, no, no, no!
Just--Just--

17:21.040 --> 17:22.476
just tell the electrician
to go home.

17:22.519 --> 17:24.260
I'll call him later.
You lock up and go home.

17:24.304 --> 17:26.132
I'll deal with it
when I get back.

17:26.175 --> 17:28.047
All right?

17:28.090 --> 17:29.613
Okay.

17:31.485 --> 17:33.443
- Everything okay?
- Yeah, it's fine.

17:33.487 --> 17:35.576
It's fine. It's just
a little problem at the shop.

17:35.619 --> 17:37.534
I should get you...home.

17:37.578 --> 17:39.971
[edgy music]

17:40.015 --> 17:41.799
I was afraid
this might happen.

17:41.843 --> 17:44.280
Six humidifiers and an AC unit
from the late '70s

17:44.324 --> 17:46.108
cranked to its lowest
setting...

17:46.152 --> 17:50.069
even in death, Benji is
a colossal pain in my ass.

17:54.203 --> 17:56.292
[dark music]

17:56.336 --> 17:58.990
- Okay. With the AC out,

17:59.034 --> 18:03.343
seems deterioration speeds
really picked up.

18:03.386 --> 18:07.260
♪

18:07.303 --> 18:10.089
[heavy exhale]

18:15.616 --> 18:19.185
Oh! Is that...ooze?

18:19.228 --> 18:20.534
[groaning]

18:20.577 --> 18:22.144
[coughing]
Things have grown

18:22.188 --> 18:24.668
biologically dire
in the Benji department.

18:24.712 --> 18:26.583
Also the rare book department.

18:26.627 --> 18:31.327
But...I can't protect them
until I get rid of him.

18:31.371 --> 18:34.156
Benji has to go.

18:34.200 --> 18:37.551
[dark music]

18:37.594 --> 18:39.248
♪

18:39.292 --> 18:41.555
[groaning]

18:49.998 --> 18:51.173
[snap]
Ugh!

18:51.217 --> 18:52.218
[phone chimes]

18:54.916 --> 18:56.874
- Hey, what are you up to?

18:56.918 --> 18:59.399
Do you happen to read Chinese?

18:59.442 --> 19:02.271
Or own a mallet?

19:02.315 --> 19:05.709
[unsettling music]

19:05.753 --> 19:07.624
- The books were safe.

19:07.668 --> 19:09.278
Basement
is 100% corpse-free.

19:09.322 --> 19:10.758
Can't burn the body
in daylight anyway,

19:10.801 --> 19:12.368
so the least Benji can do

19:12.412 --> 19:14.283
is wait in the car
for a little while.

19:14.327 --> 19:19.332
[light guitar strumming]

19:19.375 --> 19:20.463
Ready for that.
- Okay.

19:20.507 --> 19:22.552
- Let go for a second.

19:22.596 --> 19:24.772
- Okay.
- Yeah.

19:24.815 --> 19:26.426
- It's in the peg!
- Okay.

19:26.469 --> 19:28.036
[both laugh]

19:28.079 --> 19:30.778
Hand me the mallet.
- Yeah. Ah!

19:34.651 --> 19:36.218
- Should be good.

19:36.262 --> 19:39.221
[light music continues]

19:39.265 --> 19:46.750
♪

19:49.797 --> 19:52.103
- [laughing]
- There it is.

19:52.147 --> 19:53.366
Go!

19:53.409 --> 19:54.541
- [laughing]

19:54.584 --> 19:56.456
Say when.

19:58.414 --> 20:00.329
- When. I think--when.
When, when, when.

20:00.373 --> 20:01.939
- [giggling]

20:06.292 --> 20:08.816
Cheers to us.
[glasses clink]

20:08.859 --> 20:10.948
- You make a good
apprentice.

20:10.992 --> 20:15.257
- I was gonna say
the same thing about you.

20:19.174 --> 20:23.396
I'm sorry about earlier.
I didn't mean to get so upset.

20:23.439 --> 20:25.180
- [murmurs]

20:25.224 --> 20:26.877
It's okay.

20:26.921 --> 20:29.663
- No, it's not, it's just...

20:29.706 --> 20:34.058
I don't want you
to think of me

20:34.102 --> 20:37.018
like that.

20:42.371 --> 20:46.680
- I...like you, Joe.

20:46.723 --> 20:50.510
Like actually...like.

20:50.553 --> 20:54.775
[soft music]

20:54.818 --> 20:57.473
And I was a little
in my head, to be honest.

20:57.517 --> 21:01.303
Blythe's short story kinda
threw me for a loop.

21:01.347 --> 21:02.957
- It's not a competition.

21:03.000 --> 21:04.524
- I know, but...

21:04.567 --> 21:07.178
I wonder...

21:07.222 --> 21:10.791
am I ever gonna write
anything that amazing?

21:10.834 --> 21:12.836
- You're talented.

21:12.880 --> 21:14.577
- You don't know that.
- I--I know--

21:14.621 --> 21:18.102
I know you need to
get out of your head and...

21:18.146 --> 21:21.845
forget Blythe,
this Blythe person.

21:21.889 --> 21:24.108
Forget everybody.
Just write what you want.

21:24.152 --> 21:27.547
- God! Everyone says that
like it's so easy.

21:27.590 --> 21:29.505
- [laughs] I know, I know.

21:29.549 --> 21:32.203
Okay, so, um...

21:32.247 --> 21:34.075
pop quiz.

21:34.118 --> 21:35.163
Don't think.

21:36.164 --> 21:37.383
Just answer.

21:37.426 --> 21:39.123
- Okay.

21:39.167 --> 21:41.256
- What hits you
like a gut punch when you--

21:41.300 --> 21:43.084
the first thought?
[ice cubes clatter]

21:43.127 --> 21:45.086
- My dad.

21:45.129 --> 21:47.480
Before he...

21:47.523 --> 21:50.352
- Yeah. Right.

21:50.396 --> 21:52.006
Of course.

21:55.531 --> 21:57.620
- He was an addict.

21:57.664 --> 22:00.971
It was hard...

22:01.015 --> 22:03.017
and scary.

22:04.845 --> 22:07.804
I mean, there were
good days too.

22:07.848 --> 22:11.634
Like I always knew
it was gonna be one of those

22:11.678 --> 22:16.987
when I woke up to the smell
of pancakes cooking.

22:17.031 --> 22:21.470
He used this red ladle
to scoop up the batter.

22:21.514 --> 22:24.691
- This is the red ladle
story?

22:24.734 --> 22:26.954
[soft music]

22:26.997 --> 22:29.870
- And I would be...
laughing,

22:29.913 --> 22:32.481
singing along to some

22:32.525 --> 22:35.484
bad Top 40 song.

22:35.528 --> 22:38.574
And everything
would be...right.

22:38.618 --> 22:43.013
♪

22:43.057 --> 22:46.887
But then he'd...
he'd go out and...

22:46.930 --> 22:50.543
the ladle would go back
in the drawer.

22:50.586 --> 22:54.590
And I'd wait
for the next good day.

22:57.071 --> 23:01.684
Until there weren't
any more.

23:01.728 --> 23:03.251
[small laugh]

23:03.294 --> 23:05.035
Wow!

23:05.079 --> 23:08.517
I did notexpect
to say all that.

23:08.561 --> 23:10.389
- I think you're right.
You definitely don't have

23:10.432 --> 23:12.956
anything meaningful
to write about.

23:13.000 --> 23:16.525
Ohh. Benji was wrong
about all of it.

23:16.569 --> 23:19.789
His whole red ladle story.
You don't wanna be spanked.

23:19.833 --> 23:22.226
You wanna feel safe,

23:22.270 --> 23:23.706
loved.

23:23.750 --> 23:26.883
You want someone to make
pancakes for you.

23:26.927 --> 23:29.843
[quiet music]

23:29.886 --> 23:37.067
♪

23:45.511 --> 23:49.428
[lighthearted music]

23:49.471 --> 23:51.995
[knocking on door]

23:52.039 --> 23:53.388
- Um...

23:53.432 --> 23:55.651
hold that thought.
I'll be right back.

23:55.695 --> 23:58.437
[knocking continues]
Coming!

24:00.700 --> 24:03.398
Is everything okay?
- No!

24:03.442 --> 24:06.183
- Peach. I should have known.
- Thank God you're here.

24:06.227 --> 24:08.229
I'm having a really
bad flare-up.

24:08.272 --> 24:11.058
I think I need you to take me
to the emergency room.

24:12.668 --> 24:14.191
Oh...Joseph.

24:14.235 --> 24:15.932
I didn't realize you were here.

24:15.976 --> 24:18.326
- I told you he was coming.

24:18.369 --> 24:20.546
Uh, Peach
is really sick.

24:20.589 --> 24:23.418
- This is probably more
than you need to know,

24:23.462 --> 24:25.594
but...I have a rare
chronic bladder disease

24:25.638 --> 24:27.074
called interstitial
cystitis--

24:27.117 --> 24:29.468
[groans]
Oh...gosh!

24:29.511 --> 24:32.732
I mean, you know, some
people think I'm being uppity,

24:32.775 --> 24:35.517
but...I can't have
any fast food.

24:35.561 --> 24:38.694
And if I drink, it has to
be a high PH, you know,

24:38.738 --> 24:40.696
like Ketel One or Goose

24:40.740 --> 24:42.306
and pear juice.

24:42.350 --> 24:44.744
- Weren't you doing Jager
shots at your party?

24:44.787 --> 24:46.310
- Oh--oh!

24:46.354 --> 24:48.138
- Let's get you
to the hospital.

24:48.182 --> 24:50.271
- Yeah.
- And Joe has a car.

24:50.314 --> 24:51.968
He can take us.
Right, Joe?

24:52.012 --> 24:53.666
[softly]
You can take us?

24:53.709 --> 24:55.450
- Of course.

24:56.364 --> 24:58.671
I mean, I've got a dead body
in the trunk,

24:58.714 --> 24:59.846
but, hey, no biggie, right?

24:59.889 --> 25:01.456
- Oh, this is taking forever!

25:01.500 --> 25:04.328
I mean, he took the worst
street to get across town.

25:04.372 --> 25:05.721
- Be nice.

25:05.765 --> 25:07.723
- I'm in real pain!

25:07.767 --> 25:09.638
- [mouthing]
I'm sorry.

25:11.422 --> 25:13.381
- Ohh...Joseph...

25:13.424 --> 25:15.252
- Yep.
- I'm feeling nauseated.

25:15.296 --> 25:17.516
Can you crack a window?
There's like a...

25:17.559 --> 25:20.519
sort of putrid aroma that keeps
wafting in the backseat.

25:20.562 --> 25:23.478
- What can I say?
The smells of the city.

25:23.522 --> 25:26.481
[edgy music]

25:26.525 --> 25:28.527
♪

25:28.570 --> 25:29.571
- Oh...God.

25:29.615 --> 25:31.181
I can't deal.
I can't deal.

25:31.225 --> 25:33.270
We'll walk!

25:35.795 --> 25:37.536
- I'm so sorry.

25:41.975 --> 25:43.759
- It's almost
the witching hour.

25:43.803 --> 25:46.327
Grab the supplies.
Drive the narcissistic cadaver

25:46.370 --> 25:48.155
formerly known as Benji
to his final destination,

25:48.198 --> 25:52.115
light a match,
and I'm yours forever, Beck.

25:54.161 --> 25:56.772
Well, this is a development.

25:56.816 --> 25:58.557
- That's him.

25:58.600 --> 26:01.560
[intense music]

26:01.603 --> 26:03.649
♪

26:07.827 --> 26:08.828
- Potassium nitrate.

26:08.871 --> 26:10.394
Six rolls of duct tape.

26:10.438 --> 26:13.310
Fire starter, twine,
burlap, wood stakes.

26:13.354 --> 26:15.399
You wanna explain
what all this is for?

26:15.443 --> 26:17.140
- Explain the shopping list

26:17.184 --> 26:20.579
straight out of
"Body Disposal for Dummies"?

26:20.622 --> 26:22.668
I know.

26:22.711 --> 26:24.104
I know how this all must look.

26:24.147 --> 26:26.585
I know involving Paco
was the wrong thing to do.

26:26.628 --> 26:29.762
But th-things have been
a little crazy for me lately.

26:29.805 --> 26:32.721
I guess I was hoping I could
make the world a better place.

26:32.765 --> 26:36.899
[tense music]

26:36.943 --> 26:38.988
You know--It...

26:39.032 --> 26:43.123
it would--it would just
be easier if I show you.

26:44.777 --> 26:47.257
Yeah, I'll show you.
Come on.

26:49.869 --> 26:52.436
Technically, we're not allowed
to plant anything in here.

26:52.480 --> 26:55.657
I was just trying to keep it
a bit under wraps.

26:55.701 --> 26:56.789
- And the chemicals?

26:56.832 --> 26:58.529
- They dissolve roots.

26:58.573 --> 27:00.836
-Fire starters?

27:00.880 --> 27:03.273
- I like to grill.

27:05.667 --> 27:07.103
Here.

27:13.980 --> 27:15.590
- It's good.

27:15.634 --> 27:16.809
- Thank you.

27:16.852 --> 27:18.593
- So he built a garden.
So what?

27:18.637 --> 27:21.683
I told this guy--stay away
from my girlfriend's kid.

27:21.727 --> 27:25.339
And what does he do? He gives
him money for errands?

27:26.862 --> 27:28.821
- Hey, I told you,
I'm a parole officer, okay?

27:28.864 --> 27:30.518
We see guys like this
all the time.

27:30.561 --> 27:33.826
He's a sicko.
I feel it in my gut.

27:33.869 --> 27:36.567
Hey, will you get back
inside, Paco?

27:36.611 --> 27:39.179
Just tell your mom I'm gonna
be right there, okay, buddy?

27:39.222 --> 27:42.225
All right, all right,
all right.

27:42.269 --> 27:45.272
Kid's got ADHD.
Tough to manage at times.

27:45.315 --> 27:47.274
But that's what makes him
vulnerable to freaks like this.

27:47.317 --> 27:49.711
- Look, I apologize
if I crossed the line.

27:49.755 --> 27:52.714
I just noticed how hungry
Paco is all the time, you know?

27:52.758 --> 27:55.151
I gave him a few dollars
to go to the store, honestly,

27:55.195 --> 27:56.805
so he could buy himself
a sandwich.

27:56.849 --> 27:59.852
I lend him books from time
to time, too--that's all.

27:59.895 --> 28:01.984
Just seems a little neglected.

28:02.028 --> 28:04.944
- You kidding me right now?
- I'm not saying they're unfit.

28:04.987 --> 28:06.728
A lot of people drink--
- All right, that's it--

28:06.772 --> 28:08.599
- All right, all right,
all right.

28:08.643 --> 28:10.950
Sorry to have
taken up your time.

28:10.993 --> 28:12.560
Good luck with
the garden.

28:12.603 --> 28:15.650
- Thank you, Officer.
People. They're easy to fool.

28:15.694 --> 28:18.131
Like these cops. I'm the nice,
straight-edge guy.

28:18.174 --> 28:19.959
So there's nothing
to worry about.

28:20.002 --> 28:22.483
People believe whatever
supports their world-view.

28:22.526 --> 28:25.225
Unfortunately, that seems
to include you, Beck.

28:25.268 --> 28:28.576
You believed you deserved
Benji and his neglect,

28:28.619 --> 28:30.796
and you believe you deserve
Peach and her drama

28:30.839 --> 28:32.319
and on and on.

28:32.362 --> 28:34.800
I want to call and tell you,
but I can't,

28:34.843 --> 28:37.193
because there's a traditional
waiting period

28:37.237 --> 28:38.804
between every goddamn
communication

28:38.847 --> 28:40.849
when trying to date someone.

28:40.893 --> 28:43.243
I hate this generation.

28:43.286 --> 28:47.508
[unsettling music]

28:47.551 --> 28:54.515
♪

29:15.057 --> 29:16.580
- Thank you.

29:18.017 --> 29:19.279
[sighs]

29:19.322 --> 29:20.846
Thanks for
staying with me.

29:20.889 --> 29:22.978
Honestly, I...
I don't know

29:23.022 --> 29:24.806
what I would have done
without you.

29:24.850 --> 29:27.983
- You can always
count on me.

29:28.027 --> 29:29.680
- Thanks.

29:32.074 --> 29:34.642
- So what do you think
about Joe?

29:36.644 --> 29:38.951
- Uh...yeah, you know,
I like him.

29:38.994 --> 29:41.257
- I think I might
really like him.

29:41.301 --> 29:44.173
I mean, I wasn't sure
if I was ready to get involved,

29:44.217 --> 29:46.741
but...maybe?
- Okay, you can't be serious.

29:46.785 --> 29:50.963
I mean, the guy
works at a bookstore.

29:51.006 --> 29:54.836
[laughs]
Beck, look, I know you.

29:54.880 --> 29:57.186
You don't wanna spend
your fifth anniversary

29:57.230 --> 30:00.711
going Dutch
at Katz's Deli.

30:00.755 --> 30:04.019
You need someone
to take care of you.

30:04.063 --> 30:07.980
so you can write,
be free,

30:08.023 --> 30:10.025
happy.

30:10.069 --> 30:13.942
Not someone like Joe
and his financial limitations.

30:13.986 --> 30:16.075
- That is not fair.

30:16.118 --> 30:18.512
- Nobody pays me
to be fair.

30:19.121 --> 30:21.036
What do you say we get
a bite to eat?

30:21.080 --> 30:25.040
'Cause I'm starving.
- I think I better skip it.

30:25.084 --> 30:27.390
I should really
get home.

30:27.434 --> 30:29.915
Glad you're feeling
better.

30:40.926 --> 30:46.018
[phone buzzing]

30:46.061 --> 30:48.977
- Oh, no.
No, not--not now.

30:49.021 --> 30:50.936
Okay, Beck.
All right.

30:50.979 --> 30:53.068
Hey.
How's the patient?

30:53.112 --> 30:55.592
- Better.
Thanks for the ride.

30:55.636 --> 30:58.117
The doctor said it was good
that we came when we did.

30:58.160 --> 30:59.901
- Oh, yeah?

30:59.945 --> 31:03.339
- Why don't you meet me
back at my place?

31:03.383 --> 31:05.428
Maybe we can pick up
where we left off?

31:05.472 --> 31:06.821
- What about Peach?

31:06.865 --> 31:09.171
- What about her?
- Where is she now?

31:09.215 --> 31:10.433
- Indochine.

31:10.477 --> 31:12.261
It's her comfort food.

31:12.305 --> 31:14.176
[dramatic musical sting]
Joe: Perfect.

31:14.220 --> 31:16.570
Peach is gulping steamed
Chilean Sea Bass

31:16.613 --> 31:18.964
down her scrawny gullet,
and I'm about to get caught.

31:19.007 --> 31:21.270
- So...what do you think?

31:21.314 --> 31:23.185
- I think you complain about
not being able to write,

31:23.229 --> 31:24.970
but then you, you know,
drop everything

31:25.013 --> 31:27.189
for some medical emergency,
which, by the way,

31:27.233 --> 31:28.843
many believe to be
psychosomatic in origin.

31:28.887 --> 31:31.933
- I meant about you...
coming over.

31:31.977 --> 31:33.717
- I wish I could.

31:33.761 --> 31:36.024
Ha. I wish I could, but I'm
just really busy right now,

31:36.068 --> 31:37.721
so...in fact, I should go.

31:37.765 --> 31:40.115
- Look, I know Peach
showing up was bad timing,

31:40.159 --> 31:42.335
but I wasn't exactly writing
when she showed up.

31:42.378 --> 31:44.946
- No, I know.
Pro tip of the day:

31:44.990 --> 31:47.775
screen your calls when
you're trying to burn a body,

31:47.818 --> 31:49.211
because it turns out
things slip out

31:49.255 --> 31:50.821
that you didn't actually
wanna say.

31:50.865 --> 31:52.562
I don't mean to be harsh,
but...you know

31:52.606 --> 31:54.173
you're sending
some mixed messages, right?

31:54.216 --> 31:55.304
- What is that
supposed to mean?

31:55.348 --> 31:57.393
- I'm--I'm trying
to do what you want,

31:57.437 --> 31:59.352
but I-I can't tell
what that is.

31:59.395 --> 32:01.093
Like build you a bed,
be with you on the bed?

32:01.136 --> 32:02.616
Drop you down the block
because your friend

32:02.659 --> 32:04.226
is asking, and not very
politely?

32:04.270 --> 32:06.185
Seriously, Joe, shut up.
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

32:06.228 --> 32:08.927
I have to go.

32:08.970 --> 32:10.667
- But--

32:11.059 --> 32:14.584
- Hey, how's it going?
- Good.

32:14.628 --> 32:16.891
That's one hell
of a bonfire.

32:18.153 --> 32:20.547
- Yeah, what can I say?
I went a little crazy.

32:20.590 --> 32:23.637
You know what, you're welcome
to join if you like.

32:23.680 --> 32:25.334
Please say no.
Please say no.

32:25.378 --> 32:27.989
- Oh, that would be great...

32:28.033 --> 32:30.949
but we need to get back
to the car

32:30.992 --> 32:32.254
before it gets any darker.

32:32.298 --> 32:34.039
Good luck.

32:34.082 --> 32:37.738
- Yeah, have a good one!
- You too.

32:37.781 --> 32:39.000
[low chatter]

32:39.044 --> 32:41.089
man: Did you remember
where you parked?

32:42.047 --> 32:45.006
- I believe in love
at first sight.

32:45.050 --> 32:46.703
I had it with you, Beck.

32:46.747 --> 32:50.229
And maybe, just maybe,
I destroyed it

32:50.272 --> 32:55.190
just as fast, in the space
of a single phone call.

32:55.234 --> 32:58.150
Was all this for nothing?

33:02.719 --> 33:04.460
[voice echoing]
"The king and queen,

33:04.504 --> 33:06.810
when they saw their
daughter..."

33:06.854 --> 33:10.162
I've been calling Beck,
but...

33:10.205 --> 33:11.859
straight to voicemail.

33:11.902 --> 33:13.948
Worst three words
in the English language.

33:13.992 --> 33:16.995
I wonder what our kids
would have been like.

33:17.038 --> 33:19.040
They'd have grown up reading,
not glued to iPads,

33:19.084 --> 33:20.520
and we definitely
wouldn't have named them

33:20.563 --> 33:22.261
things like Gulliver
or Blaze

33:22.304 --> 33:23.740
or Misti with an "i."

33:23.784 --> 33:27.048
We would have crushed this.
Together.

33:27.092 --> 33:30.356
It wasn't supposed to
end like this.

33:30.399 --> 33:33.185
Call me back, Beck.

33:33.228 --> 33:34.882
The end.

33:34.925 --> 33:37.841
[somber music]

33:37.885 --> 33:42.716
♪

33:42.759 --> 33:45.327
[trailing applause echoes]

33:46.328 --> 33:49.288
- I don't mean this to blow
smoke up your ass or anything,

33:49.331 --> 33:51.725
but your writing
makes me think

33:51.768 --> 33:54.336
that Raymond Carver
has been reincarnated.

33:54.380 --> 33:56.904
- That is so kind of you
to say, Tomas.

33:56.947 --> 33:59.428
I was born in '88,
the year he died,

33:59.472 --> 34:01.126
so, weirdly enough,

34:01.169 --> 34:03.084
you're not the first
person to have said that!

34:03.128 --> 34:06.914
- Again, great work, Blythe.
Excited to see what's next.

34:06.957 --> 34:08.481
Beck, we weren't
expecting you.

34:08.524 --> 34:10.135
You didn't send along pages.

34:10.178 --> 34:12.093
- I know. I'm sorry.

34:12.137 --> 34:14.400
And I'm sorry I'm late.
It's just...

34:14.443 --> 34:17.403
I wrote them, but they
sounded super emo.

34:17.446 --> 34:18.926
So I wrote them up
and started over,

34:18.969 --> 34:21.189
and I lost track of time,
but, uh...

34:21.233 --> 34:23.670
this...feels like me

34:23.713 --> 34:26.847
and what I want to say.

34:28.153 --> 34:30.459
It's only one page, but--

34:30.503 --> 34:32.113
- That isn't really enough
for us to critique.

34:32.157 --> 34:35.725
- Are we supposed to
read it now...in front of you?

34:35.769 --> 34:37.553
[laughs] That's...
kind of awkward.

34:37.597 --> 34:39.468
- If that's the case,
I should warn you,

34:39.512 --> 34:40.991
I have this facial autism thing

34:41.035 --> 34:42.384
where I can't hide
what I'm thinking.

34:42.428 --> 34:44.734
[light laughter]
- Let's just reschedule

34:44.778 --> 34:47.824
your review
for another time.

34:51.045 --> 34:54.004
[somber music]

34:54.048 --> 35:00.881
♪

35:11.021 --> 35:12.240
- Beck?

35:12.284 --> 35:14.895
- [inaudible]

35:14.938 --> 35:16.418
Hey.

35:17.680 --> 35:19.334
Uh...okay, so I hate
to admit it,

35:19.378 --> 35:20.988
but you were right.

35:21.031 --> 35:22.468
A little bit.

35:22.511 --> 35:24.687
I will do anything
for my friends,

35:24.731 --> 35:26.298
and do I hide behind them--
yeah.

35:26.341 --> 35:28.735
And do I use them as
an excuse not to write?

35:28.778 --> 35:31.129
Honestly, I'd use anything
as an excuse not to write,

35:31.172 --> 35:34.741
because...okay,
I'm afraid I might fail--

35:34.784 --> 35:36.656
one terrible page away

35:36.699 --> 35:39.093
from confirming I'm the worst
writer in history.

35:39.137 --> 35:42.705
All of that to say
if I'm sending mixed messages,

35:42.749 --> 35:46.448
it's because...
I don't know who I am.

35:46.492 --> 35:48.972
So how am I supposed to
know what I want?

35:49.016 --> 35:51.627
And I know--I know
I sound super gross,

35:51.671 --> 35:54.195
like so...
I don't know--millennial.

35:54.239 --> 35:56.589
Don't say anything.

35:56.632 --> 35:58.634
- In this moment,
you are everything.

35:58.678 --> 36:00.201
- Here's the thing.

36:00.245 --> 36:04.205
If you know who you are,
it's not like you share it.

36:04.249 --> 36:08.775
I mean, you're a Nice Guy with
the "You are remarkable" stuff

36:08.818 --> 36:11.430
and Feelings Guy with the
"Write what moves you."

36:11.473 --> 36:13.954
But then [lowers voice]
you try and go down on me

36:13.997 --> 36:15.303
in the middle
of a furniture store.

36:15.347 --> 36:16.739
If I didn't know better,

36:16.783 --> 36:18.785
I'd think you were hiding
something.

36:18.828 --> 36:21.788
For God's sakes, why are you
holding a Pendleton blanket?

36:24.312 --> 36:27.489
I've never even seen
your place.

36:27.533 --> 36:30.492
And you never talk about
any of your friends.

36:30.536 --> 36:32.842
I mean, who are you?

36:35.018 --> 36:38.457
Okay, that was too much.
Um...

36:38.500 --> 36:40.372
It sounded better
in my head.

36:40.415 --> 36:42.852
I wanna show you something.

36:42.896 --> 36:46.291
[soft, sweeping music]

36:46.334 --> 36:49.511
♪

36:49.555 --> 36:52.340
You wanna know me, Beck?

36:54.386 --> 36:56.779
[hinges squeal]

36:56.823 --> 36:59.695
I'll show you
exactlywho I am.

36:59.739 --> 37:03.133
[dark music]

37:03.177 --> 37:07.312
♪

37:07.355 --> 37:09.662
[ominous musical sting]

37:09.705 --> 37:12.665
[intense buildup]

37:18.366 --> 37:21.674
- This is where we keep
the rarest books--

37:21.717 --> 37:24.329
the collectibles,
first editions.

37:24.372 --> 37:27.375
[soft music]

37:27.419 --> 37:30.422
♪

37:30.465 --> 37:32.380
It's paper, cloth, leather,

37:32.424 --> 37:35.557
paste.
It's all vulnerable.

37:35.601 --> 37:37.690
All sensitive to light,

37:37.733 --> 37:39.518
humidity, temperature.

37:39.561 --> 37:43.391
[soft music continues]

37:43.435 --> 37:45.393
That's why...

37:45.437 --> 37:48.178
they need to be in here.

37:49.484 --> 37:51.443
[softly]
To protect them.

37:53.488 --> 37:55.185
I can take you
to my apartment.

37:55.229 --> 37:57.753
Anytime you want.

38:01.540 --> 38:03.455
I want you to meet
my friends, I do.

38:03.498 --> 38:07.110
But this...

38:07.154 --> 38:08.721
this right here

38:08.764 --> 38:12.986
is the most important
place in the world to me.

38:13.595 --> 38:17.425
As weird as it sounds...

38:17.469 --> 38:21.560
these books are more alive,

38:21.603 --> 38:24.737
more...worthy

38:24.780 --> 38:27.043
than most people I know.

38:29.002 --> 38:33.006
You wanna know who I am,
this is it.

38:33.049 --> 38:37.271
[sweeping, emotional music]

38:37.315 --> 38:44.670
♪

38:54.506 --> 38:56.377
- There you are.

38:56.421 --> 39:00.163
- That's it. I am officially
out of the Tinder business.

39:00.207 --> 39:02.383
- [small laugh]
Bravo, honey.

39:02.427 --> 39:05.386
- I just--Oh, I feel like
this is a good step, you know?

39:05.430 --> 39:07.606
Like this is good for me.

39:07.649 --> 39:09.999
Joe is good for me.

39:10.043 --> 39:11.958
- Whatever you need,
Becks.

39:12.872 --> 39:16.441
No, I'm just saying--
and I mean this, honestly--

39:16.484 --> 39:19.487
maybe a simple life
isn't so bad.

39:19.531 --> 39:21.010
Maybe it's what you need.

39:21.054 --> 39:22.838
Maybe I should be
looking for that.

39:22.882 --> 39:25.406
- Joe isn't simple.
He's...he's different.

39:25.450 --> 39:27.756
Complicated.

39:27.800 --> 39:30.411
- That's funny...

39:30.455 --> 39:32.021
there's a book missing.

39:32.065 --> 39:35.373
- Really?
What book is that?

39:35.416 --> 39:36.678
- "Ozma of Oz."

39:36.722 --> 39:38.898
Huh. It was just here.

39:38.941 --> 39:41.509
Joe was looking at it
at my party.

39:41.553 --> 39:43.859
- I'm sure it'll turn up.

39:43.903 --> 39:46.514
[edgy, anticipatory music]

39:46.558 --> 39:52.825
♪

39:54.653 --> 39:57.656
- You've deleted Tinder,
and now you've called

39:57.699 --> 39:59.745
and asked me to come over.

39:59.788 --> 40:05.925
My faith in our epic love
story is officially restored.

40:05.968 --> 40:07.579
- I'm sorry, Joe.
I'm so stupid.

40:07.622 --> 40:10.886
I left your list on my bed,
and Ron found it.

40:10.930 --> 40:13.019
I'm sorry.
- You're not stupid.

40:13.062 --> 40:16.457
It's not your fault.
- I tried to explain, but...

40:16.501 --> 40:19.460
- It's not your fault!

40:19.504 --> 40:20.635
[sighs]

40:20.679 --> 40:22.898
Guys like Ron are bullies.

40:22.942 --> 40:26.598
We just need to stay
one step ahead of them.

40:26.641 --> 40:29.949
Like the Musketeers--always
one step ahead of the Cardinal.

40:29.992 --> 40:31.385
Right?

40:31.429 --> 40:33.474
One for all...

40:33.518 --> 40:36.042
- And all for one.

40:37.522 --> 40:38.479
- Paco!

40:38.523 --> 40:40.394
Get inside.

40:40.438 --> 40:44.746
- I can smell the bourbon
from here.

40:44.790 --> 40:46.748
- I told you...

40:46.792 --> 40:48.924
leave the kid alone.

40:48.968 --> 40:50.578
Look, you may have
the cops fooled

40:50.622 --> 40:52.711
with your bullshit
tomato garden,

40:52.754 --> 40:54.800
but I'm right.

40:54.843 --> 40:57.846
There's something wrong
with you.

40:57.890 --> 41:00.370
I see it in your eyes.

41:03.722 --> 41:05.375
[scoffs]

41:05.419 --> 41:08.466
[dark music]

41:08.509 --> 41:09.554
[door slams]

41:09.597 --> 41:11.730
- File that away
[phone chimes]

41:11.773 --> 41:13.079
under future problems.

41:13.122 --> 41:14.559
Beck: Knock, knock.
You here yet?

41:14.602 --> 41:16.735
Joe: Because tonight...
[upbeat music]

41:16.778 --> 41:20.260
tonight I show you...
I'm The One.

41:20.303 --> 41:28.355
♪

41:52.640 --> 41:56.296
[pop music continues]

41:56.339 --> 42:03.390
♪

42:10.092 --> 42:11.877
- Oh--
[music stops]

42:12.617 --> 42:14.575
[groans]

42:14.619 --> 42:18.492
[shuddering breaths]

42:18.536 --> 42:20.799
- Did you just...
